<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Around what level is this clockwork?</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Some Info</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-01 19:55:46</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok, here's the skinny on the CWG Model EXG:  Contrary to someone's post above, IT IS totally immune to magic.  It is a tall (about the size of a wood elf) female clockwork that roams near the front gate of the gnomish castle.  It's placeholder can be any roaming clockwork, but it is usually a CWS model SX (the only clockwork spider there is in sol a).  The EXG is around level 28 or 29, and hits for around 65 damage max.  Unless you are a melee class or a pet class you really don't have a chance to solo it until it is most likely green to you.  A level 39 druid can "porcupine" it (cast both your coat and shield spells and let it pound on you until it dies, while hitting it with melee and healing yourself)  A level 40 or so cleric with close to max melee skills should be able to melee it to death, healing when necessary.  The CGS is the common drop, and loads around 80% of the time (the EXG will have it equipped if she has it)  The rest of the time the EXG will load the Charred Guardian Breastplate (16 ac +3 str +6 sta)  One more thing to consider when fighting the EXG:  It resists ALL spells, including root/snare.  So, if it starts to run, you better kill it quick before it runs into the goblin infested area of sol a (a big problem unless you are a dwarf who worships Brell, they start out with indifferent faction to the goblins)</font></td></tr></table>
